<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Findex is a highly customizable application finder written in Rust. It uses GTK and focuses on performance</p> <p>Findex v0.6.0 comes with vast improvements. This release isn&#39;t supposed to change the look of Findex that much. However, Findex was rewritten to have a better codebase in this release. Because of this, the performance of Findex has increased significantly. Check out the release page to see changelog.</p> <p>Release: <a href="https://github.com/mdgaziur/findex/releases/tag/v0.6.0">https://github.com/mdgaziur/findex/releases/tag/v0.6.0</a></p> <p>Currently I&#39;m very busy taking preparation for upcoming exam. So, I took shortcut and decided to use systemd to restart findex when configurations change. I&#39;ll properly implement it in next release.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/mdgaziur001"> /u/mdgaziur001 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w163zo/announcing_findex_v060/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w163zo/announcing_findex_v060/">[comments]</a></span>